comments.body:
It looks like a work around for the issue in QA runs is to modify the read timeout for internal services:

{code}
# euca-modify-property -pbootstrap.webservices.client_internal_timeout_secs=90
{code}

The default is 60 seconds and for some reason the cluster controller takes just over 60 seconds to respond to an unassign request with this use case (terminate as soon as running). This causes the cloud controller to roll back its internal state (reassign the address) with the intent of cleaning it up later. The cloud controller is then failing to later retry the clean up, leaving the address assigned (EUCA-6124 has been opened for the cluster controller issue)
